sentences: Tereza Ana Kesovija (pronounced [terěːza âna kesǒʋija]; born 3 October 1938) is an internationally acclaimed Croatian recording artist.
In 1962, shortly after the start of her professional career, she won her first international contest at Saint-Vincent, Italy.
She spent 1963 and 1964 touring USSR, Poland, Finland, Denmark, Germany, Switzerland, Norway and Sweden.
In 1965, she moved to France, although she did not speak French.
In 1967, she made the first recording of "La chanson de Lara" (Lara's Theme) from the film Doctor Zhivago.
With the song "Bien plus fort", Tereza was chosen by Grace Kelly to represent Monaco in the Eurovision 1966.
In 1968, Kesovija performed with Enrico Macias at the L'Olympia in Paris.
It was her second Olympia after 1966.
During the 1970s, Tereza became world-known star representing Yugoslav and French song worldwide.
In Yugoslavia, she was honored with Best Female Singer of the Year Award six years in a row (1974–79).
In 1972, she represented Yugoslavia in the Eurovision Song Contest with "Muzika i ti" (The Music and You).
In 1978, she returned to with her interpretation of "Je suis née ce jour-là".
During the 1980s, she continued to tour all around the world.

She was honoured with the Best Yugoslav Female Singer of the Year award for several times and she realised golden, platinum and diamond records, but the most important event was in 1988, when she performed at Olympia Hall in Paris.
Kesovija finished the 1980s touring in Scandinavia and representing Yugoslavia national football team on Italian TV during the World Cup.
In the decade following the breakup of Yugoslavia in 1991, there were wars all over the former Yugoslavia, including the Croatian War of Independence between 1991 and 1995.
In the decade following the breakup of Yugoslavia in 1991, there were wars all over the former Yugoslavia, including the Croatian War of Independence between 1991 and 1995.
Jacques Chirac honored Tereza in 1999 with Knighthood of High Decoration of Arts and Culture.
In 2002, her concert from Olympia was realized on CD edition.
That 2002 is important year in her career, because she had some concerts together with Oscar and Grammy winner, Michel Legrand.
In 2005, Kesovija celebrated 45 years of her career with a concert Mojih 45 skalina in Vatroslav Lisinski Concert Hall.
Her fourth concert at the Olympia Concert Hall was realized in 2007.
After 2008 she was toured Slovenia, Macedonia, Croatia, and Bosnia and Herzegovina.
In 2010, she celebrated 50 years onstage with a concert "Još se srce umorilo nije" at Zagreb's Lisinski Concert Hall.
In 2011, she decided to come back in Serbia and Montenegro.
